>
	<p>
		I'm Skittles, currently a grade 2024 student in Industrial Automation, School of Electrical Engineering, 
		Xi'an Jiaotong University. I'm also minoring in Japanese, expecting to fetch a second Bachelor's degree.
		I started this blog as a personal space to document my journey, share my projects, write down my 
		daily thoughts as well as record my emotions. Balancing a heavy engineering schedule with language learning
		is not always easy, but I really enjoy how studying Japanese gives me a fresh, creative perspective outside
		of my main major.
		
	</p>

	<p>
		A large part of my time is spent dealing with the technical side of things. I love the hands-on process 
		of engineering——whether it is designing hardware, soldering circuits, or debugging microcontrollers late 
		into the night. Aside from my regular coursework, I also enjoy using my coding skills, especially vibe ones
		to analyze financial markets and test quantitative trading strategies. Recently I'm trying using For me, there is a unique satisfaction 
		in taking a complex problem, breaking it down into data, and building a working system from scratch.
	</p>

	<p>
		When I need a break from all the screens, wires, and formulas, I always turn to music. I have been 
		playing the piano for a long time, and classical music is my ultimate escape. Whenever I feel stressed 
		after a long day of debugging, sitting down to practice a challenging Chopin etude or a powerful 
		Beethoven sonata helps me clear my mind and relax. I also recommend traditional Chinese music like Erquan 
		Yingyue (The Moon Reflected on the Second Spring) or Pi Huang. It is a completely different way of thinking 
		compared to engineering, allowing me to focus on expression rather than just strict logic.
	</p>

	<p>
		Outside of schoolwork and music, I have a couple of other hobbies that keep life interesting. I am 
		deeply fascinated by astronomy, so I love taking my camera outside on clear nights to stargaze and
		capture photos of different constellations. On the weekends, my focus usually shifts to football. 
		I am a massive fan of Manchester United & Wuxi Wugo and I do not just watch the games for fun——I love 
		analyzing the manager's tactical choices. I sometimes watch F1 races. Red Bull Racing and Verstappen are
		my favourite. 
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is basically a collection of all these different pieces of my life. Whether you are here 
		to read about engineering projects, musical insights, or just casual updates, I hope you find 
		something enjoyable. Thanks for stopping by, and feel free to look around!
	</p>
</Layout>
